{"_id":"7f832460-446f-322b-9fcd-59936615714a","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"28dde5772b48c92e08b8050411aa5ba8","message":"Regarding logging, QBWI will log exceptions automatically. My AspNetBackgroundTasks will not; you'd have to add your own exception catching and logging code to whatever delegate you pass to Run.\r\n\r\nA 401 error showing up in a load-balanced environment is usually due to keeping session state in-memory instead of in distributed storage. It certainly wouldn't have anything to do with the type of background task technology you're using.","postId":"2014_06_fire-and-forget-on-asp-net-006b7bdf-c89c-3ee5-bcd5-a85f62b3a22c","replyTo":"5fedfc9e-3e60-3c43-953d-f46291b0eb95","date":"2017-09-28T21:57:14Z","timestamp":1506635834,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"}